Package logic

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICustomer
    The ICustomer interface represents a customer entity with basic information such as name, contact details, and user type.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AmountDivisionReport
    The AmountDivisionReport class represents a report containing park amount summary data.
    CancellationsReport
    The CancellationsReport class represents a report containing cancellation data for park daily summaries.
    ClientConnection
    The ClientConnection class is an entity which contains the client information.
    ClientRequestDataContainer
    A container class for storing client request data.
    ClientRequestHandler
    Handles client requests for the server application, routing each request to the appropriate handler method based on the type of request.
    Employee
    The Employee class represents an employee user within the system.
    EntitiesContainer
    The EntitiesContainer class is a container for storing multiple entities and an optional customer interface.
    ExternalUser
    The ExternalUser class represents a user of type "ExternalUser".
    Guide
    The Guide class represents a user who is also a guide.
    GuideInTable
    The GuideInTable class represents a guide's information formatted for display in a table view.
    Order
    Represents an order for a visit to a park.
    OrderInTable
    Represents an order in a table format.
    Park
    Represents a park entity.
    ParkAmountSummary
    Represents a summary of park visit amounts.
    ParkDailySummary
    Represents a summary of daily park statistics.
    ParkFullDaySummary
    Represents a summary of park occupancy for a specific hour.
    Report
    Represents a report with specific parameters.
    Request
    Represents a request made for a park.
    RequestInTable
    Represents a request in a format suitable for display in a table.
    SceneLoaderHelper
    The SceneLoaderHelper class provides utility methods for loading FXML-based views into JavaFX scenes.
    ServerResponseBackToClient
    Represents a response sent from the server back to the client, containing a server response object and a message.
    UsageReport
    Represents a usage report, extending the base Report class, containing data and summaries for park usage.
    User
    Represents a user in the system, extending the ExternalUser class and implementing Serializable.
    Visitor
    Represents a visitor, extending the ExternalUser class and implementing the ICustomer interface.
    VisitsReport
    The VisitsReport class represents a report containing information about visits and idle times.
